==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heterocarpism
<hw>Het`er*o*car"pism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The power of producing two kinds of reproductive bodies, as in the
hog peanut <spn>Amphicarpaea bracteata</spn>, in which besides the usual
pods produced from flowers above ground, there are others underground.
In the hog peanut the above-ground flowers are all creamy white or
tinged with purple, as in the photo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heterocarpous</ent>⟦br⟧
